name:           gitllm
version:        0.1.0.0
synopsis:       MCP server exposing granular git operations for LLM tooling
description:    gitllm is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that exposes a comprehensive
                suite of git operations as discrete, scoped tools. Designed for LLM agents
                that need fine-grained, safe access to git repositories — covering everything
                from basic status queries to advanced rebase, worktree, and submodule workflows.
